verbose_text: We have explicitly highlighted several useful information and facts like : i) No established relationship between progression of SARS-CoV-2 with temperature, humidity and/or both, ii) The underlying mechanism of SARS-CoV-2 is not fully understood, iii) Respiratory droplet size determines drop and airborne based transmission, iv) Prognosis of COVID-19 can be done by its effects on various body organs, v) Infection can be stopped by restricting the binding of S protein and AE2, vi) Hydroxychloroquine is believed to be better than chloroquine for COVID-19, vii) Ivermectin with Vero-hSLAM cells is able to reduce infection by ~ 5000 time within 2 days, and viii) Nafamostat mesylate can inhibit SARS-CoV-2 S protein initiated membrane fusion.
evidence: binding of S protein and AE2
